    Tests: 47/47 Spaarke.Scheduling (delta +5 from 42); 17/17 BFF Admin (delta +6 from 11).
    BFF build: 0 errors, 16 pre-existing warnings unchanged. Scheduling lib builds clean (TreatWarningsAsErrors).
    Publish size: 44.86 MB compressed (delta -1.32 MB vs 46.18 baseline; no new NuGet adds).
    CVE: no new HIGH-severity CVE (only pre-existing Microsoft.Kiota.Abstractions 1.21.2).
    Design decisions:
      - Fire-and-track mechanism: Task.Run with CancellationToken.None for the dispatched task
        (admin client cancellation cancels dispatch path only, NOT in-flight runs — host shutdown
        drain via _inFlight tracking is the correct cancel surface per NFR-07).
      - JobNotFoundException location: Spaarke.Scheduling (not BFF) so any consumer of TriggerNowAsync
        catches the same type without taking a BFF dependency.
      - TriggerResult vs TriggerResponse: Spaarke.Scheduling owns TriggerResult (shared-lib contract);
        BFF owns TriggerResponse (wire-DTO with sibling DTOs in Api/Admin/Models/). Endpoint maps
        between them. Preserves single-direction dependency (BFF → shared-lib, never reverse).
      - ScheduledJobHost singleton (NOT hosted-service) registration: TriggerNowAsync works without
        the cron loop running. First production cron migration (task 023+) adds AddHostedService.
        Avoids paying for an idle cron loop in P3 deployments when no cron jobs exist yet.
      - Manual triggers persist scheduledFireUtc=null per IBackgroundJobStore contract; no idempotency
        dedup applied (admin double-click = 2 runs by design).
      - Retry policy applies uniformly to manual triggers (same RetryPolicy as scheduled).
      - Caller-supplied parameter overrides merge ON TOP OF definition's persisted ConfigJson
        (overrides win on key conflict).
    Coordination with tasks 022: pre-marked "===== Task 022 =====" comment block in JobsEndpoints.cs
    reserves handler slot. Task 022 will add GET /history + POST /enable + POST /disable without
    touching task 020 or 021 handlers / helpers.
    adr-check (self): PASS — ADR-001 (in-process), ADR-008 (RequireAuthorization at MapGroup),
    ADR-010 (singleton concrete + interface only justified by ≥2 impls), ADR-029 (publish measured),
    ADR-032 N/A (host is unconditional). bff-extensions §A/§C/§F/§F.1: PASS.
    Not committed per task brief.
